com.xuggle.xuggler.io
Interface IURLProtocolHandlerFactory

All Known Implementing Classes:
FileProtocolHandlerFactory, NullProtocolHandlerFactory, XugglerIO
public interface IURLProtocolHandlerFactory

Used by URLProtocolManager to get a factory for a given protocol. Implement this interface on any factories that make your specific implementation of IURLProtocolHandler, and then register the factory with your URLProtocolManager

Method Summary
 IURLProtocolHandler getHandler(String protocol, String url, int flags)
          Called by FFMPEG in order to get a handler to use for a given file.
 

Method Detail

getHandler

IURLProtocolHandler getHandler(String protocol,
                               String url,
                               int flags)
Called by FFMPEG in order to get a handler to use for a given file.

Parameters:
protocol - The protocol without a ':'. For example, "file", "http", or "yourcustomprotocol"
url - The URL that FFMPEG is trying to open.
flags - The flags that FFMPEG will pass to IURLProtocolHandler.open(String, int)
Returns:
A IURLProtocolHandler to use, or null. If null, a file not found error will be passed back to FFMPEG.
